"signal_description": "The SIGNAL query is selecting three columns from a subquery: 'Document Type', 'Payment Time', and 'No. of Invoices'. The subquery is performed on the table 'defaultview-529'. The 'Document Type' column in the subquery is derived from the 'Inv. Document Type Text' column of the 'defaultview-529' table. The 'Payment Time' column is calculated as the average difference between the last 'END_TIME' where the 'EVENT_NAME' is 'Clear Invoice' and the first 'END_TIME' where the 'EVENT_NAME' is 'Create Invoice'. The 'No. of Invoices' column is the count of 'case_id'. The subquery only includes rows where the 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' is earlier than the 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date'. The subquery results are ordered by the second column in descending order. The main query then filters out any rows from the subquery where 'Payment Time' is null."
